                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <strong>River Sports in Himachal Pradesh
                    <o:p>:</o:p>
          </strong></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    The snow and rain-fed perennial rivers of Beas, Ravi, Sutlej and Chenab flow rapidly down the slopes and this speed is what makes river rafting thrilling. Popular white water rafting sites in Himachal Pradesh are :
                      <o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    1.
                    Beas near Kullu<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    2.
                    Sutlej near Shimla<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    3.
                    Ravi near Chamba<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    4.
                    Chenab (also known as Chandrabhaga) in Lahaul<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;
                    </p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    The <em>best</em> white water rafting site is the 20 kilometers long area on the Beas River from <strong>Shamsi to Aut</strong> in <strong>Kullu</strong> district.
<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    You can also check out the tributaries of the Beas River (Chaki, Suheti, Luni, Uhl, Banganga, Parvati, Sainj and Hurla) and the Spiti River (Sutlej River merges with this river while entering the Spiti Valley) for white water rafting. The difficulty level of rafting in these rivers is from IV to VI. Only professionals are advised to raft since this is a dangerous sport. But if you are interested and physically fit, you can enroll at the Atal Bihari Vajpayee Institute for Mountaineering and Allied Sports in Manali and learn the basics of white water rafting. They also provide intermediate and advanced courses for all water sports. You can hire rafting gear from the Himachal Pradesh Tourism office.<o:p></o:p></p>
